{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858083675,"sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","part":{"id":"prt_d7963d79b001w6sbaRYdOvdzhV","messageID":"msg_d7963cdc3001P6tm004nVuCrUZ","sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8e09c69769b1404290f101f9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/store  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement Valkey storage backend for the pkg/store module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [x] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Implement Valkey storage backend\n15: - [ ] Add unit tests\n16: - [ ] Add integration tests\n17: \n18: ## Notes\n19: \n20: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n21: \n22: ## Source Files\n23: \n24: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n**Module:** pkg/store  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Valkey storage backend for the pkg/store module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [x] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Implement Valkey storage backend\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/README.md","time":{"start":1775858083659,"end":1775858083674}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858083677,"sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","part":{"id":"prt_d7963dd1f0019vZ29FOzA1sdtL","messageID":"msg_d7963cdc3001P6tm004nVuCrUZ","sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_eaced34317af4ed09a2bba53","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Valkey Store Structure\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n20:   - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:\n21:     - `cli valkey.Client` (from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n22:     - `sessionPrefix string`\n23:     - `expiryIndexKey string`\n24:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string`\n25: \n26: ### Phase 2: Connection Configuration\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` function\n29:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable (required, comma-separated)\n30:   - Split by `,` → `InitAddress` slice\n31:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variable\n32:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default `\"true\"`, case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"`)\n33:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, if true → `DisableCache=true`)\n34:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, if true → `ForceSingleClient=true`)\n35:   - Return `*valkey.ClientOption`\n36:   - Error if `VALKEY_ADDR` empty or password required but empty\n37: \n38: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewValkeyStore()` constructor\n39:   - Takes `*valkey.ClientOption`\n40:   - Creates Valkey client via `valkey.NewClient()`\n41:   - Returns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"...\", expiryIndexKey: \"...\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"...\"}`\n42:   - Error on client creation failure\n43: \n44: ### Phase 3: Core Store Methods\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `valkeyStore.Ping()` method\n47:   - Execute `B().Ping()` command\n48:   - Expect string response `\"PONG\"`\n49:   - Return error if not PONG\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` method\n52:   - Construct key: `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n53:   - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n54:   - If `IsValkeyNil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n55:   - Unmarshal bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n56:   - Return error on unmarshal failure\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` method\n59:   - Validate: sandbox not nil, `ExpiresAt` not zero\n60:   - Construct session key\n61:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n62:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomic operations:\n63:     - `SETNX` session key with JSON\n64:     - `ZADD expiryIndexKey` with score=`ExpiresAt.Unix()`, member=sessionID\n65:     - `ZADD lastActivityIndexKey` with score=`time.Now().Unix()`, member=sessionID\n66:   - Check all responses for errors\n67:   - Return error if SETNX fails (key already exists)\n68: \n69: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` method\n70:   - Construct session key\n71:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n72:   - Execute `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx()` (key must exist)\n73:   - If response != `\"OK\"` → return `ErrNotFound`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` method\n76:   - Construct session key\n77:   - Use `DoMulti`:\n78:     - `DEL` session key\n79:     - `ZREM expiryIndexKey` member=sessionID\n80:     - `ZREM lastActivityIndexKey` member=sessionID\n81:   - Check all responses for errors\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` method\n84:   - If `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil`\n85:   - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n86:   - Get session IDs from result\n87:   - Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n88:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo`\n89: \n90: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()` method\n91:   - Same as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but on `lastActivityIndexKey`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` method\n94:   - Validate: sessionID non-empty\n95:   - If `at` is zero time → use `time.Now()`\n96:   - Construct session key\n97:   - Execute `Exists` key → must return 1\n98:   - If 0 → return `ErrNotFound`\n99:   - Execute `Zadd` with timestamp score\n100:   - Return error on failure\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `valkeyStore.Close()` method\n103:   - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n104:   - Return nil\n105: \n106: ### Phase 4: Helper Functions\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper\n109:   - Takes `[]string` session IDs\n110:   - Build all `session:{id}` keys\n111:   - Use single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n112:   - Add code comment: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n113:   - Unmarshal JSON, skip empty strings (orphaned ZSET members)\n114:   - Log warnings via `klog.Warningf()` for orphaned/invalid entries\n115:   - Return `[]*types.SandboxInfo, error`\n116: \n117: ### Phase 5: Testing (TDD)\n118: \n119: #### Unit Tests - Configuration\n120: \n121: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n122:   - Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with all env vars set\n123: \n124: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with missing `VALKEY_ADDR`\n125:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR` not set\n126:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n127:   - Then: returns error\n128: \n129: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with comma-separated addresses\n130:   - Given: `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2,addr3\"`\n131:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n132:   - Then: `InitAddress = [\"addr1\", \"addr2\", \"addr3\"]`\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n135:   - Given: `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"`\n136:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n137:   - Then: `DisableCache=true`\n138: \n139: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n140:   - Given: `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"`\n141:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n142:   - Then: `ForceSingleClient=true`\n143: \n144: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with password required but empty\n145:   - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n146:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n147:   - Then: returns error\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TEST-007**: Test `makeValkeyOptions()` with `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n150:   - Given: `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"`\n151:   - When: `makeValkeyOptions()` called\n152:   - Then: returns options with empty password\n153: \n154: #### Unit Tests - Store Methods\n155: \n156: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Mock test `valkeyStore.Ping()` returns PONG\n157:   - Given: mocked Valkey client returning PONG\n158:   - When: `Ping()` called\n159:   - Then: returns nil error\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TEST-011**: Mock test `valkeyStore.GetSandboxBySessionID()` with missing key\n162:   - Given: `IsValkeyNil` true\n163:   - When: `GetSandboxBySessionID()` called\n164:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **TEST-012**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with nil sandbox\n167:   - Given: `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n168:   - When: called\n169:   - Then: returns error\n170: \n171: - [ ] **TEST-013**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` with zero ExpiresAt\n172:   - Given: sandbox with `ExpiresAt.IsZero() = true`\n173:   - When: called\n174:   - Then: returns error\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TEST-014**: Mock test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` DoMulti atomicity\n177:   - Given: valid sandbox\n178:   - When: `StoreSandbox()` called\n179:   - Then: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity all called\n180: \n181: - [ ] **TEST-015**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n182:   - Given: SET XX returns not \"OK\"\n183:   - When: `UpdateSandbox()` called\n184:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **TEST-016**: Mock test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` DoMulti\n187:   - Given: existing session\n188:   - When: `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` called\n189:   - Then: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity all called\n190: \n191: - [ ] **TEST-017**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` with limit 0\n192:   - Given: `limit = 0`\n193:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n194:   - Then: returns `nil, nil`\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-018**: Mock test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()` tolerates orphaned keys\n197:   - Given: ZSET returns IDs but some MGET return empty\n198:   - When: `ListExpiredSandboxes()` called\n199:   - Then: skips missing keys, returns found ones\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TEST-019**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with missing session\n202:   - Given: Exists returns 0\n203:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n204:   - Then: returns `ErrNotFound`\n205: \n206: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with zero time\n207:   - Given: `at = time.Time{}`\n208:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n209:   - Then: uses `time.Now()` for ZADD score\n210: \n211: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Mock test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with empty sessionID\n212:   - Given: `sessionID = \"\"`\n213:   - When: `UpdateSessionLastActivity()` called\n214:   - Then: returns error\n215: \n216: #### Integration Tests\n217: \n218: - [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey_integration_test.go`\n219:   - Requires Docker Valkey or testcontainers\n220: \n221: - [ ] **TEST-031**: Integration test `valkeyStore.Ping()` with real Valkey\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TEST-032**: Integration test `valkeyStore.StoreSandbox()` → `GetSandboxBySessionID()`\n224:   - Store sandbox\n225:   - Retrieve by session ID\n226:   - Verify fields match\n227: \n228: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSandbox()` XX semantics\n229:   - Store sandbox\n230:   - Update sandbox\n231:   - Verify updated fields\n232:   - Try update non-existent → expect `ErrNotFound`\n233: \n234: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Integration test `valkeyStore.DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` cleanup\n235:   - Store sandbox\n236:   - Delete\n237:   - Verify GET returns `ErrNotFound`\n238:   - Verify ZSETs don't contain session ID\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListExpiredSandboxes()`\n241:   - Store multiple sandboxes with different expiry times\n242:   - Query with `before` time\n243:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n244: \n245: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Integration test `valkeyStore.ListInactiveSandboxes()`\n246:   - Store multiple sandboxes, update some with `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n247:   - Query with `before` time\n248:   - Verify correct sandboxes returned\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TEST-037**: Integration test ZSET index consistency under concurrent operations\n251:   - Multiple goroutines Store/Delete concurrently\n252:   - Verify ZSET indices remain consistent\n253: \n254: - [ ] **TEST-038**: Integration test `valkeyStore.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` full flow\n255:   - Store sandbox\n256:   - Update last activity\n257:   - Verify ZSET score updated\n258: \n259: - [ ] **TEST-039**: Integration test with password authentication\n260:   - Start Valkey with password\n261:   - Configure `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n262:   - Verify connection succeeds\n263: \n264: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Integration test with comma-separated addresses\n265:   - Configure `VALKEY_ADDR=\"addr1,addr2\"`\n266:   - Verify client connects to cluster\n267: \n268: ### Phase 6: Documentation\n269: \n270: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add godoc comments to `valkeyStore` struct\n271:   - Document purpose and fields\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to `makeValkeyOptions()`\n274:   - Document all environment variables\n275:   - Document default values\n276:   - Document error conditions\n277: \n278: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Add godoc comments to `NewValkeyStore()`\n279:   - Document parameters and return values\n280: \n281: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add godoc comments to all `valkeyStore` methods\n282:   - Document Valkey API patterns used\n283:   - Document DoMulti atomicity guarantees\n284:   - Document error conditions including `ErrNotFound`\n285: \n286: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Document key patterns in code comments\n287:   - `session:{id}` for JSON storage\n288:   - `session:expiry` ZSET for expiry index\n289:   - `session:last_activity` ZSET for activity index\n290: \n291: - [ ] **DOC-006**: Document ZSET score semantics\n292:   - Expiry score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n293:   - Last activity score = `LastActivityAt.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n294: \n295: - [ ] **DOC-007**: Add code comment to `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()`\n296:   - Document MGET cluster slot consideration\n297:   - Note: \"Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments\"\n298: \n299: - [ ] **DOC-008**: Document environment variables in code comments or README\n300:   - All `VALKEY_*` variables\n301:   - Default values and required status\n302:   - Case-insensitivity notes\n303: \n304: - [ ] **DOC-009**: Add example usage in doc.go or example test\n305:   - Initialize Valkey store via `NewValkeyStore()`\n306:   - Call `Ping()` to verify connectivity\n307:   - Call `StoreSandbox()` to persist sandbox\n308:   - Call `GetSandboxBySessionID()` to retrieve\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## Acceptance Criteria\n313: \n314: - [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n315: - [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n316: - [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n317: - [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n318: - [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n319: - [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n320: - [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n321: - [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n322: - [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n323: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n324: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n325: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n326: - [ ] `Storage()` singleton supports `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Dependencies\n331: \n332: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n333: |------------|--------|-------|\n334: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n335: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n336: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | `SandboxInfo` type |\n337: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo alias source |\n338: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Internal | Store interface (AR-012) |\n339: \n340: ---\n341: \n342: ## Implementation Order\n343: \n344: ```\n345: TASK-001\n346:     ↓\n347: TASK-010 → TASK-011\n348:     ↓\n349: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → ... → TASK-028\n350:     ↓\n351: TASK-030\n352:     ↓\n353: TEST-001 → ... → TEST-040\n354:     ↓\n355: DOC-001 → ... → DOC-009\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Related ARs\n361: \n362: | AR | Title | Relationship |\n363: |----|-------|--------------|\n364: | AR-012 | Session Storage Interface Definition | Base interface work |\n365: | AR-013 | Redis Storage Implementation | Parallel Redis backend |\n366: | AR-014 | Valkey Storage Implementation | This implementation |\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n  - Define `valkeyStore` struct with fields:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775858083662,"end":1775858083675}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858083680,"sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","part":{"id":"prt_d7963e26d001mvAUBThOFZ6rIJ","messageID":"msg_d7963cdc3001P6tm004nVuCrUZ","sessionID":"ses_2869ca873ffee9VLuhkaCWmjfs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4d0b616f18174885a346e4a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey Store Implementation\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Type:** New Feature\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This specification defines the Valkey implementation of the `Store` interface for session persistence in the AgentCube sandbox orchestration system. The Valkey store provides an alternative backend to Redis with compatible operations using the `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Requirements\n17: \n18: ### R-1: Valkey Store Structure\n19: \n20: **Given** the Valkey store implementation  \n21: **When** the store is instantiated  \n22: **Then** it SHALL have the following structure:\n23: \n24: ```go\n25: type valkeyStore struct {\n26:     cli                  valkey.Client\n27:     sessionPrefix        string\n28:     expiryIndexKey       string\n29:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n34: \n35: ```gherkin\n36: Scenario: Valkey store has correct fields\n37:   Given the valkeyStore struct is defined\n38:   When the struct is inspected\n39:   Then it SHALL have cli field of type valkey.Client\n40:   And it SHALL have sessionPrefix string field\n41:   And it SHALL have expiryIndexKey string field\n42:   And it SHALL have lastActivityIndexKey string field\n43: \n44: Scenario: Valkey store uses same key patterns as Redis\n45:   Given valkeyStore constants are defined\n46:   When the values are checked\n47:   Then sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n48:   And expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n49:   And lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### R-2: Valkey Client Connection Options\n55: \n56: **Given** Valkey store initialization  \n57: **When** connection options are built  \n58: **Then** the system SHALL construct `valkey.ClientOption` with:\n59: \n60: - `InitAddress`: Split from `VALKEY_ADDR` by commas\n61: - `Password`: From `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n62: - `DisableCache`: From `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n63: - `ForceSingleClient`: From `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n64: \n65: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n66: \n67: ```gherkin\n68: Scenario: Single address InitAddress\n69:   Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"valkey:6379\"\n70:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n71:   Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"valkey:6379\"}\n72: \n73: Scenario: Multiple addresses InitAddress\n74:   Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379\"\n75:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n76:   Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"node1:6379\", \"node2:6379\", \"node3:6379\"}\n77: \n78: Scenario: Password provided\n79:   Given VALKEY_PASSWORD=\"secret123\"\n80:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n81:   Then Password SHALL be \"secret123\"\n82: \n83: Scenario: DisableCache enabled\n84:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"\n85:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n86:   Then DisableCache SHALL be true\n87: \n88: Scenario: DisableCache disabled\n89:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"false\"\n90:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n91:   Then DisableCache SHALL be false\n92: \n93: Scenario: DisableCache invalid value\n94:   Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"invalid\"\n95:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n96:   Then DisableCache SHALL be false (ParseBool fallback)\n97: \n98: Scenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n99:   Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\n100:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n101:   Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n102: \n103: Scenario: ForceSingleClient disabled\n104:   Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE unset\n105:   When makeValkeyOptions is called\n106:   Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be false\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ### R-3: Valkey Environment Variables\n112: \n113: **Given** Valkey store initialization  \n114: **When** environment variables are read  \n115: **Then** the system SHALL require/process:\n116: \n117: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n118: |----------|----------|-------|\n119: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list |\n120: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n121: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | Default `true`, case-insensitive |\n122: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n123: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n124: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n125: \n126: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n127: \n128: ```gherkin\n129: Scenario: VALKEY_ADDR required\n130:   Given VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n131:   When Valkey store initializes\n132:   Then initialization SHALL fail with error indicating missing VALKEY_ADDR\n133: \n134: Scenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD required by default\n135:   Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n136:   And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED is unset\n137:   When Valkey store initializes\n138:   Then initialization SHALL fail with error stating password required\n139: \n140: Scenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD disabled\n141:   Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n142:   And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\n143:   When Valkey store initializes\n144:   Then connection SHALL proceed with empty password\n145: \n146: Scenario: STORE_TYPE must be valkey\n147:   Given STORE_TYPE=\"redis\"\n148:   When Valkey store initialization is attempted\n149:   Then the Redis implementation SHALL be selected instead\n150: \n151: Scenario: STORE_TYPE case insensitive\n152:   Given STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"\n153:   When Storage() initializes\n154:   Then Valkey implementation SHALL be constructed\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ### R-4: Ping Operation\n160: \n161: **Given** a Valkey store instance  \n162: **When** `Ping(ctx)` is called  \n163: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n164: \n165: - Execute `B().Ping()` command\n166: - Expect string response `PONG`\n167: - Return error if response is not `PONG`\n168: \n169: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n170: \n171: ```gherkin\n172: Scenario: Ping succeeds\n173:   Given a healthy Valkey server\n174:   When Ping(ctx) is called\n175:   Then B().Ping() SHALL be executed\n176:   And the response SHALL be \"PONG\"\n177:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n178: \n179: Scenario: Ping fails\n180:   Given Valkey server is unreachable\n181:   When Ping(ctx) is called\n182:   Then B().Ping() SHALL return error\n183:   And non-nil error SHALL be returned\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ### R-5: GetSandboxBySessionID Operation\n189: \n190: **Given** a session ID  \n191: **When** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n192: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n193: \n194: - Construct key as `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n195: - Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n196: - Return `ErrNotFound` if `IsValkeyNil` is true\n197: - Decode JSON bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo` on success\n198: \n199: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n200: \n201: ```gherkin\n202: Scenario: Get existing session\n203:   Given session \"abc-123\" exists with valid JSON data\n204:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n205:   Then B().Get().Key(\"session:abc-123\") SHALL be executed\n206:   And JSON SHALL be decoded to *types.SandboxInfo\n207:   And the SandboxInfo SHALL be returned with nil error\n208: \n209: Scenario: Get missing session\n210:   Given no key \"session:abc-123\" exists\n211:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n212:   Then IsValkeyNil SHALL return true\n213:   And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n214: \n215: Scenario: Get with invalid JSON\n216:   Given key \"session:abc-123\" contains invalid JSON\n217:   When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n218:   Then JSON decoding SHALL fail\n219:   And appropriate error SHALL be returned\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### R-6: StoreSandbox Operation\n225: \n226: **Given** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo`  \n227: **When** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n228: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n229: \n230: - Reject nil sandbox with error\n231: - Reject zero `ExpiresAt` with error\n232: - Execute `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n233: - Use `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` for expiry score\n234: - Use `float64(time.Now().Unix())` for last-activity score\n235: \n236: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n237: \n238: ```gherkin\n239: Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n240:   Given StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\n241:   When the method executes\n242:   Then error SHALL indicate sandbox is nil\n243:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n244: \n245: Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n246:   Given sandbox with ExpiresAt = time.Time{}\n247:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n248:   Then error SHALL indicate ExpiresAt is invalid\n249:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n250: \n251: Scenario: StoreSandbox succeeds\n252:   Given valid sandbox with SessionID=\"abc\", ExpiresAt=Unix(1000)\n253:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n254:   Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n255:     | Command | Key | Member | Score |\n256:     | SETNX | session:abc | - | - |\n257:     | ZADD | session:expiry | abc | 1000 |\n258:     | ZADD | session:last_activity | abc | <now.Unix()> |\n259:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n260: \n261: Scenario: Duplicate store fails\n262:   Given session \"abc\" already exists\n263:   When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with same SessionID is called\n264:   Then SETNX SHALL return 0\n265:   And error SHALL be returned\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### R-7: UpdateSandbox Operation\n271: \n272: **Given** an existing session  \n273: **When** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n274: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n275: \n276: - Execute `SET` with `XX` option (key must exist)\n277: - Require response `\"OK\"` for success\n278: - NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries\n279: \n280: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n281: \n282: ```gherkin\n283: Scenario: Update existing session\n284:   Given session \"abc\" exists with JSON value V1\n285:   When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with updated data is called\n286:   Then SET session:abc value XX SHALL be executed\n287:   And response SHALL be \"OK\"\n288:   And JSON value SHALL be updated to V2\n289:   And session:expiry and session:last_activity SHALL be unchanged\n290: \n291: Scenario: Update missing session\n292:   Given session key \"session:abc\" does not exist\n293:   When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n294:   Then SET XX SHALL not update (key missing)\n295:   And response SHALL not be \"OK\"\n296:   And error SHALL be returned indicating key not exists\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ### R-8: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Operation\n302: \n303: **Given** a session ID  \n304: **When** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n305: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n306: \n307: - Execute `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n308: - Remove session from all three storage locations\n309: \n310: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n311: \n312: ```gherkin\n313: Scenario: Full removal\n314:   Given session \"abc\" exists in main key and both ZSETs\n315:   When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n316:   Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n317:     | Command | Key | Member |\n318:     | DEL | session:abc | - |\n319:     | ZREM | session:expiry | abc |\n320:     | ZREM | session:last_activity | abc |\n321:   And all three operations SHALL succeed\n322:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n323: \n324: Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n325:   Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n326:   When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n327:   Then DEL and ZREM operations SHALL complete without error\n328:   And nil error SHALL be returned (idempotent)\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ### R-9: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n334: \n335: **Given** a time `before` and limit  \n336: **When** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n337: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n338: \n339: - Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n340: - Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix())`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n341: - Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n342: - Skip orphaned ZSET members (missing JSON keys)\n343: \n344: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n345: \n346: ```gherkin\n347: Scenario: List expired sessions\n348:   Given session:expiry contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n349:   And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n350:   When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n351:   Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n352:   And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n353:   And MGET SHALL load JSON for each member\n354:   And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n355: \n356: Scenario: Zero limit\n357:   Given limit = 0\n358:   When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n359:   Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n360: \n361: Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n362:   Given session:expiry contains \"orphan\" but no session:orphan key\n363:   When ListExpiredSandboxes loads sessions\n364:   Then \"orphan\" SHALL be omitted from results\n365:   And no error SHALL be returned for the orphan\n366: ```\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ### R-10: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n371: \n372: **Given** a time `before` and limit  \n373: **When** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n374: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n375: \n376: - Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n377: - Execute `Zrangebyscore` on `session:last_activity` with same parameters as expired\n378: - Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n379: - Skip orphaned ZSET members\n380: \n381: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n382: \n383: ```gherkin\n384: Scenario: List inactive sessions\n385:   Given session:last_activity contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n386:   And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n387:   When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n388:   Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n389:   And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n390:   And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n391: \n392: Scenario: Zero limit\n393:   Given limit = 0\n394:   When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n395:   Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ### R-11: UpdateSessionLastActivity Operation\n401: \n402: **Given** a session ID and timestamp  \n403: **When** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called  \n404: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n405: \n406: - Reject empty session ID with error\n407: - Use `time.Now()` if `at` is zero time\n408: - Verify session key exists using `Exists` (must return 1)\n409: - Execute `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with `float64(at.Unix())`\n410: - Return `ErrNotFound` if session key does not exist\n411: \n412: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n413: \n414: ```gherkin\n415: Scenario: Empty session ID rejected\n416:   Given UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now()) is called\n417:   When the method executes\n418:   Then error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n419:   And no backend operation SHALL occur\n420: \n421: Scenario: Update last activity\n422:   Given session \"abc\" exists\n423:   And at = Unix(2000)\n424:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n425:   Then Exists(\"session:abc\") SHALL return 1\n426:   And ZADD session:last_activity abc 2000 SHALL be executed\n427:   And nil error SHALL be returned\n428: \n429: Scenario: Zero time uses Now\n430:   Given session \"abc\" exists\n431:   And at = time.Time{} (zero value)\n432:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n433:   Then ZADD SHALL use time.Now().Unix() as score\n434: \n435: Scenario: Update missing session\n436:   Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n437:   When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Now()) is called\n438:   Then Exists SHALL return 0\n439:   And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n440:   And no ZADD SHALL occur\n441: ```\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ### R-12: Close Operation\n446: \n447: **Given** a Valkey store instance  \n448: **When** `Close()` is called  \n449: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n450: \n451: - Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n452: - Return `nil`\n453: \n454: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n455: \n456: ```gherkin\n457: Scenario: Close connection\n458:   Given valkeyStore with active client connection\n459:   When Close() is called\n460:   Then vs.cli.Close() SHALL be executed\n461:   And nil SHALL be returned\n462: ```\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ### R-13: ZSET Score Semantics\n467: \n468: **Given** ZSET operations for indices  \n469: **When** scores are assigned  \n470: **Then** the system SHALL use:\n471: \n472: - **Expiry index:** `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\n473: - **Last activity index:** `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`, `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n474: \n475: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n476: \n477: ```gherkin\n478: Scenario: Expiry score from ExpiresAt\n479:   Given sandbox.ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)\n480:   When StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n481:   Then score SHALL be 1234567890.0\n482: \n483: Scenario: Last activity score from current time\n484:   Given StoreSandbox is called at time.Unix(1000, 0)\n485:   When last-activity index is updated\n486:   Then score SHALL be 1000.0\n487: \n488: Scenario: Last activity score from provided time\n489:   Given UpdateSessionLastActivity with at = time.Unix(2000, 0)\n490:   When last-activity index is updated\n491:   Then score SHALL be 2000.0\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ### R-14: MGET Optimization Note\n497: \n498: **Given** loading multiple sessions by IDs  \n499: **When** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` is called  \n500: **Then** the implementation SHALL:\n501: \n502: - Build all `session:{id}` keys\n503: - Use single `MGET` command for batch retrieval\n504: - Note: Keys should be in same cluster slot for deployment consideration\n505: \n506: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n507: \n508: ```gherkin\n509: Scenario: Batch load with MGET\n510:   Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] all exist\n511:   When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n512:   Then single MGET session:a session:b session:c SHALL be executed\n513:   And all three SHALL be loaded efficiently\n514: \n515: Scenario: Partial MGET results\n516:   Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] where only \"a\" and \"c\" exist\n517:   When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n518:   Then MGET SHALL return values for \"a\", \"\", \"c\"\n519:   And only \"a\" and \"c\" SHALL be in returned slice\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ---\n523: \n524: ## Dependencies\n525: \n526: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n527: |------------|--------|-------|\n528: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n529: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging in makeValkeyOptions |\n530: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo type |\n531: \n532: ---\n533: \n534: ## Data Structures\n535: \n536: ### valkeyStore\n537: \n538: ```go\n539: type valkeyStore struct {\n540:     cli                  valkey.Client\n541:     sessionPrefix        string\n542:     expiryIndexKey       string\n543:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n544: }\n545: ```\n546: \n547: ### Environment Configuration\n548: \n549: ```go\n550: type ValkeyConfig struct {\n551:     Addr                 string   // VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated)\n552:     Password             string   // VALKEY_PASSWORD\n553:     PasswordRequired     bool     // VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED (default true)\n554:     DisableCache         bool     // VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE (default false)\n555:     ForceSingleClient    bool     // VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE (default false)\n556: }\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ## Files to Create/Modify\n562: \n563: | File | Action | Description |\n564: |------|--------|-------------|\n565: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Create | Valkey implementation of Store interface |\n566: | `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for Valkey operations |\n567: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Modify | Add valkeyStoreType constant and Valkey initialization |\n568: \n569: ---\n570: \n571: ## Testing Strategy\n572: \n573: 1. **Unit Tests**:\n574:    - Mock Valkey client with gock/valkey mock\n575:    - Test all failure modes (connection errors, nil responses)\n576:    - Test environment variable parsing\n577: \n578: 2. **Integration Tests**:\n579:    - TestContainer with Valkey instance\n580:    - Verify all Store interface operations\n581:    - Test ZSET score semantics\n582: \n583: 3. **Compatibility Tests**:\n584:    - Verify same behavior as Redis implementation\n585:    - Test identical GIVEN/WHEN/THEN outcomes\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## Security Considerations\n590: \n591: - **Password Storage**: Loaded from environment variable (never committed)\n592: - **Connection**: TLS recommended for production Valkey connections\n593: - **Logging**: Password values MUST NOT be logged (use klog carefully)\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## Open Questions\n598: \n599: 1. Should cluster mode be explicitly supported with slot hashing?\n600: 2. Should connection pooling parameters be configurable?\n601: 3. Should Valkey-specific features (e.g., JSON module) be leveraged?\n\n(End of file - total 601 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey Store Implementation\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New Feature\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis specification defines the Valkey implementation of the `Store` interface for session persistence in the AgentCube sandbox orchestration system. The Valkey store provides an alternative backend to Redis with compatible operations using the `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### R-1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n**Given** the Valkey store implementation  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858083664,"end":1775858083677}}}}
